Subject: [PATCH 2/3] slub: don't use cpu partial pages on UP
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

commit b39ffbf8b14de2e7c1679462313cf32abb7ef463 upstream

MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

cpu partial pages are used to avoid contention which does not exist in
the UP case. So let SLUB_CPU_PARTIAL depend on SMP.

Acked-by: Christoph Lameter <cl@linux.com>
Signed-off-by: Uwe Kleine-KÃ¶nig <u.kleine-koenig@pengutronix.de>
Signed-off-by: Pekka Enberg <penberg@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: De Huo <De.Huo@windriver.com>
---
 init/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/init/Kconfig b/init/Kconfig
index 4444b2e..b9bc910 100644
--- a/init/Kconfig
+++ b/init/Kconfig
@@ -1597,7 +1597,7 @@ endchoice
 
 config SLUB_CPU_PARTIAL
 	default y
-	depends on SLUB
+	depends on SLUB && SMP
 	bool "SLUB per cpu partial cache"
 	help
 	  Per cpu partial caches accellerate objects allocation and freeing
